OL,6,F"Of course they come to school and
OL,7,Fchallenge us on particular things, and
OL,8,Fso they should. I think the best
OL,9,Fparents are the ones who come in, they
OL,10,Fquestion, they challenge, they ask us
OL,11,Fthings, they want to know answers,
OL,12,Fthey disagree with things.
OL,14,F"The most difficult parents are the
OL,15,Fones we can't get ahold of. But there
OL,16,Fare ways and means to challenge, and
OL,17,Fthere is no place for aggression. No
OL,18,Fplace at all."
